/*!
\page string_regexprep REGEXPREP Regular Expression Replacement Function

<p>
Section: \ref sec_string "String Functions"
\section Usage
Replaces regular expressions in the provided string.  The syntax for its
use is 
\verbatim
  outstring = regexprep(instring,pattern,replacement,modes)
\endverbatim
Here <tt>instring</tt> is the string to be operated on.  And <tt>pattern</tt> is a regular
expression of the type accepted by <tt>regexp</tt>.  For each match, the contents
of the matched string are replaced with the replacement text.  Tokens in the
regular expression can be used in the replacement text using <tt>$N</tt> where <tt>N</tt>
is the number of the token to use.  You can also specify the same <tt>mode</tt> 
flags that are used by <tt>regexp</tt>.
*/
